subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Holotype
10 mm
long for 64 chaetigers, body dark brown. Prostomium embedded into peristomium, with two minute antennae (
Fig. 17A, B
). Proboscis expanded as sucker, with many minute cilia on its inner surface (
Fig. 17A, C, D
). First segment achaetous, with two pairs of tentacular cirri (
Fig. 17A–D
). Parapodial lobes of chaetiger 1 shorter than followers, lacking ventral cirri and bearing two elliptical dorsal projections (
Fig. 17A–C
). All following parapodia biramous, with ventral lamella on their bases (
Figs 17F
, 
18A, B
). Notopodia with spindle-shaped dorsal cirri (
Fig. 18A, B
) and a single acicula (
Fig. 18C
); notochaetae present from chaetiger 5 onwards, short, capillary, very finely spinulose (
Fig. 18E
). Neuropodia with postchaetal lobe mucronated (
Fig. 18D
); with about 20 compound chaetae decreasing in size ventrally (
Fig. 18F–H
). Pygidium simple, without anal cirri (
Fig. 17E
).
